title: Version 0.2.7
message: Version 0.2.7

title: version 0.2.6a
message:
version 0.2.6a
final push for 0.2.6, includes new weapon enchantments, blinded enemy changes and more.

title: v02.6: All the Cool Kids are doing it!
message:
v02.6: All the Cool Kids are doing it!
- look for the jewelry chain in the prison rooms
- items remain visible in the dungeon after they are seen
- new Holy and Hunting weapon enchantments
- enchantment description updates
- killing wraiths can now get you a reward
- slightly more special rooms per level
- food drops reduced slightly
- blinded creatures are now blind
- mindless mobs not affected by psionics
- graphics tweaks
- fix for the Rankings Screens
- Bug fixes

title: v02.5: Beta Test Version
message:
v02.5: Beta Test Version
- class rebalincing
- made mini-bosses tougher
- tweaked open level spawn rates
- reduced frequency of open levels

title: v02.3: Badges and More!
message:
v02.3: Badges and More!
- new room blocked with eternal flame
- fire damage scales slightly with depth
- new mini-bosses in infinite levels
- fixed some badge balance issues
- standardized graphics on some badges
- new badge just for Beta Testers
- donation rewards are now easier to reach
- throwing potions at mobs affect them
- ring of searching now affects search speed
- flavor text on tombstones
- Endless mode goes past depth 31
- stop the hero from ascending in Endless mode

title: version 0.2.2
message:
version 0.2.2
- Added in Endless mode (must defeat 4th boss)
   - shops every 10th level on the 1's
   - mini-boss and donation altars on the 5's
   - boss battle on the 10's
   - new theme ever 5 levels (graphics and monster set)
   - mobs scaled to dungeon depth
- Added in Test mode (return to surface with amulet)
- fixed some typos

title: Version 0.2.1
message:
Version 0.2.1
- list rings in the catalogue
- added potions of haste and slowness
- added a few new mobs (dungeon snakes and velocirooster)
- tweaked how potions affect hunger

title: DSM-0064   tutorial level messages
message:
DSM-0064   tutorial level messages

NOTE - the MessageSpot.java was a failed experiment that made it into one of the builds.
There is a slight chance that saved Tutorial level games from the interim build may die
horribly when reloaded... so I am going to wait until after I either test the removal fully
or have given enough time so that (virtually) no one will be effected prior to removal.
You should not pick up this file in your builds unless you want to play with the functionality.
